The paper is about a portfolio solver for Constraint Programming, which is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The use of multicore technology is a key aspect of the paper, which suggests that it could also be relevant to Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of different solvers and their performance, which could be of interest to researchers in Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Programming Languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper presents empirical results and discusses the implementation of the solver, which suggests that it could also be relevant to Software Engineering (cs.SE).
